The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Trinamul man killed
                                                                                                               Trinamul man killed
                            
	Chinsurah, June 3: Suspected CPM supporters today burnt a Trinamul Congress leader alive in Hooghlys Khanakul, a Left stronghold.        
	Police said over 100 peo- ple armed with scythes and spears stormed Judhistir Doluis house at 3.30pm after pl-anting red flags around it.         
	The attackers beat up his wife Chhaya when she tried to douse his flames. Their sons Abhijeet, 16, and Asim, 13, were also not spared.         
	Firemen from Arambagh town, 30km away, reached in an hour. The police came half-an-hour after that, though they had to travel 22km.         
	Trinamul leader Samir Bhandari said Judhistir, 45, was their main organiser in the area. The party has called a 12-hour bandh in the Arambagh subdivision tomorrow.        
	The CPM admitted the attackers were its supporters but said the murder was the result of a family feud.                                                                                                                                                                              
